text: Food was decent. Its Indonesian Chinese fusion food. However the price is a tad expensive. Ordered the economical noodles with a fried egg, vegetables and a begadil and was charged $5 as shown in the picture. No meat at all. Pricing is always inconsistent.
Had a simple $8 delicious lunch at Xiang Geli. It's not easy to find a reasonably priced lunch at Serangoon Gardens.
